cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.LG 

The paper discusses a quantitative model of behavior changes in response to feedback in social media, drawing on inverse reinforcement learning and studies of human game playing. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, given the focus on social interactions and feedback, cs.SI and cs.CY are the most likely sub-categories.
